metadata.name: Glass is class #329
metadata.description:
Warning: GPU intensive stuff!

may perform badly on lower-end GPUs...

only 512 editions are available, I reserved 512 more just in case some previews don't render correctly...the unminted reserves will be burned.

hold the left mouse button and drag to rotate the view around the center

hover with your mouse to spawn some settings controls:
 - Resolution (performance-heavy)
 - Light bounces
 - Frame Samples
 - Screenshot Button (takes a screenshot...if it doesn't download, you should open the generator in a new tab)

Technique: Pathtracing
Lib: ThreeJS (React Three Fiber)

metadata.name: When Light Meets Water #82
metadata.description:
For #tezosartweek 13-19 June 2022

Made with p5.js.

Keys
- 1: view 1000px png (Default)
- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.

metadata.name: A creative tunnel that leads to nothing #30
metadata.description:
This piece is dedicated to all those forgotten projects that have been left behind, maybe they were just simple ideas that didn't stick, or maybe full blown complex creations, never completed, never released...just stuff on the walls of a tunnel that ends into nothing.

Goodbye.

Time to move on.

#tezosartweek

metadata.name: Hotline #214
metadata.description:
--CONTROLS--

[S]: Save PNG
[Z]: Zoom
[F]: Fullscreen
[L]: Light

------------

Focus, dedication
Allowing yourself to be

Break the pattern to see what is left,
when you have nothing to hold on to.

This is about making choices
Removing the noise
Looking inwards
Transcendence

The only real hotline you have
is the connection with yourself

------------

released under CC BY-NC 4.0.

Tijn Arts, 2022

metadata.name: SWTBD - construction drawing #5
metadata.description:
Construction drawing of the "Several ways to break down" generative geometry system by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut

mouse:

click: toggle active mode. In active mode, a new iteration with the same starting geometry and identical features is generated every 10s.

keyboard:

'a' or 'A' : add a slice or point
'e': decrease explosion factor
'E': increase explosion factor
'r' or 'R': create a new iteration with the same starting geometry and identical features
'+' and '-': zoom in and out
arrow keys: rotate around and translate along the vertical axis

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #360
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden â€œtemplateâ€ canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden â€˜templateâ€™ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: indefinite parabola #27
metadata.description: The lines, starting from the main one, smoothly spread over the canvas, creating completely unique patterns. The essence of the art work is its uncertainty (as, for example, in quantum mechanics). As long as you don't mint, the parabola will point up and down at the same time. There is also a chance to get a straight line, complementing the uniqueness of the generation.
